      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis power-law threshold sensitivity — at chosen C_th",
      "description": "Sensitivity of predicted RH to the hemolysis power-law threshold coefficient C_th evaluated at C_th = 1.8 × 10⁻⁵ (Giersiepen correlation). Predicted RH across all 5 operating points remained within ±8% of experimental measurements at the chosen settings. The package does not pin C_th for deployment; analysts selecting an alternative correlation coefficient (e.g., Heuser–Opitz C_th = 3.62 × 10⁻⁷) would obtain materially different RH predictions without triggering re-assessment under the current documentation.",
      "quantityOfInterest": "Relative hemolysis index (RH)",
      "metricValue": 0.08,
